First, make sure your device has a GPS chip and that the GPS is enabled. You can do this by going to your device's Settings app, then selecting "Location" or "Connections," and toggling the switch next to "GPS" to the "On" position.

Next, you'll need to use a programming language like Java or Kotlin to access the GNSS timestamp. You can do this by using the Android LocationManager class, which provides methods for getting the current location and timestamp.

